title: SFH on pharmaceutical issues
content_text:
p>
Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Secretary for Food and 
Health, Dr York Chow, at a stand-up media session at Legislative Council 
Building today (March 11): Reporter: (Loopholes in the system in monitoring) Secretary for Food and Health: I think the Department of Health has 
proactively discovered the irregularity of the labelling of the drugs. In 
fact, they are actually doing their job and taking actions to rectify the 
situation with the pharmaceutical company. The pharmaceutical company

situation with the pharmaceutical company. The pharmaceutical company 
actually withdraws some of the products, so this is something that the 
Department of Health will need to give more factual explanation this 
afternoon. Reporter: (No need to tell the public?) Secretary for Food and Health: The Department of Health is actually going 
through the process of investigation on something relating to quality and 
not on safety. They need to get out the fact from the company before they 
can make any announcement. So this is the reason why and we are still going

can make any announcement. So this is the reason why and we are still going 
through the process right now. I think the Department of Health will be able 
to explain the situation and process later on. Reporter: Is it necessary to diversify the suppliers concerning drugs? Secretary for Food and Health: I said earlier that the Hospital Authority, 
particularly the biggest consumer of pharmaceutical in Hong Kong, does not 
actually procure the pharmaceutical from a single source for every drug. But 
for Metformin, this is something that they have done. They also have to

for Metformin, this is something that they have done. They also have to review that in the future, this type of big volume medication, they should consider having suppliers from more than one source. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript.)
